# Retro Platformer Conventions

This is a **sample Cursor rule** for demo purposes. Rules in `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` give the AI persistent project context.

## Project shape

- Static browser game: `index.html`, `style.css`, `game.js`
- No build step, no external game engines or npm dependencies
- Canvas logical resolution: 480×270, scaled via CSS + `devicePixelRatio`

## Code style

- Keep game logic in `game.js`; use section headers like `// === Input ===`
- Prefer plain classes/objects over frameworks
- Match existing naming: `TILE`, `LOGIC_W`, `aabbOverlap`, `Save.get/set`

## When editing gameplay

```javascript
// ✅ GOOD — extend existing systems
this.particles.coinBurst(x, y);
this.audio.sfxCoin();

// ❌ BAD — don't add image assets or bundlers for this project
import sprite from './hero.png';
```

## Physics & feel

- Preserve coyote time, jump buffer, and forgiving hitboxes (~70% width)
- New juice (particles, screen shake, squash-stretch) should reuse `ParticleSystem` and `Camera.addShake`
- Procedural levels must stitch chunk seams cleanly (no floating ground gaps)

## Audio

- Use `AudioEngine` Web Audio synthesis only — no external sound files
- Respect mute state from `localStorage` key `platformer_muted`

## Persistence

- High score / best level keys: `platformer_highscore`, `platformer_bestlevel`
- Do not rename these without a migration note
